            "metadata": {
                "abstract": "Motivation: Pairwise relatedness plays an important role in a range of genetic research fields. However, currently only few estimators exist for individuals that are admixed, i.e. have ancestry from more than one population, and these estimators fail in some situations.Results: We present a new software agent, RelateAdmix, for obtaining maximum likelihood estimates of pairwise relatedness from genetic data between admixed individuals. We show using simulated data that it gives rise to better estimates than three state-of-the-art software agents, REAP, KING and Plink, while still being fast enough to be applicable to large datasets. Â© 2013 The Author 2013. Published by Oxford University Press. All rights reserved.",
